    "122757336": {
      "title": "Spatially accurate dissipative or conservative finite difference schemes deriived by the discrete variational method",
      "abstract": "A method, called “the discrete variational method”, has been recently presented by Furihata and Matsuo for designing finite difference schemes that inherit energy dissipation or conservation property from nonlinear partial differential equations (PDEs). In this paper the method is enhanced so that the derived schemes should be highly accurate in space by introducing higher order spatial difference operators, including the so-called “spectral differentiation” operator. Applications to the KdV equation, and the cubic nonlinear Schrodinger equation are also presented."
